
Just say for sake of saying its for a shop:
Holds an account of everything that the shop has in stock

When people buy things updates stock num
When delivery is made updates stock num
Option to add item or update manually
Option to remove item manually
Shows stock number on page
Add in functionality for user and staff.
Track whats been sold, onto staff interface auto updated or shown as report

What were using: Django Framework
Pages:
    Login{
        Authentication
        Create User(customer)
    }
    Customer interface(shop){
        Search Bar
        Table of items
        Basket shown
        Checkout
    }
    Staff interface{
        Create User(Staff)
        Table sold products
        Alerts for low stock
        Delivery place     
    }
    Checkout{
        Uses basket
        Takes details and pays
        Store transaction
    }
    

